<article id="node-16959">
<h1 >3.4.8.40 RAFS - Assessment under the Farmers&#039; Income Test</h1>
<p><strong>Note:</strong> THIS SCHEME CLOSED on 31 July 2001 and the following INFORMATION is FOR HISTORICAL PURPOSES ONLY.</p>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>This section explains how the farmer's income is assessed for the farmers' income test (<a href="../../../1/1/f/120">1.1.F.120</a>).</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="30">3.4.8.30</a> RAFS - Farmers' Income Test</p>
</div>
<h2>Assessment of income</h2>
<p>The following table explains the application of the farmers' income test in different circumstances:</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Example No.</th>
<th scope="col">If a qualifying farmer…</th>
<th scope="col">Then the…</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1</td>
<td>was partnered at the time of divestment,</td>
<td>partnered farmers' income test is to be used.</td>
</tr><tr><td>2</td>
<td>was partnered at any time in the 3 years prior to divestment, but is no longer partnered,</td>
<td>partnered farmers' income test is to be used</td>
</tr><tr><td>3</td>
<td>has become a member of a couple after giving the farm to the younger generation,</td>
<td>income of the new partner is NOT included in any calculations relating to the farmers' income test.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4</td>
<td>is separated due to ill health at the time of divestment,</td>
<td>applicable rate under the farmers' income test will be twice the <a href="../../../acronyms#mbr" title="Maximum basic rate">MBR</a> for a person who is not a member of a couple (whether of the same sex or a different sex). Income and assets will still be assessed as for a member of a couple.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><div class="example">
<p><strong>Example 1:</strong> A widowed farmer remarried in 1997 and now wishes to give the farm to his child and the child's partner, so that he and his new partner can retire. As he was partnered at the time he gave the farm to his child, both his and his new partner's income will be assessed in the 3 financial years prior to divestment. They will be able to have combined income up to twice the amount of MBR for a partnered person.</p>
</div>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example 2:</strong> A farmer died in 1997, leaving the farm to his widow. She gave the farm to her children in 1998, and applies for Age under RAFS. Although she was not a member of a couple (whether of the same sex or a different sex) at the time she gave the farm to her children, her income alone, not including any income her partner received before he died, will still be assessed. She will be able to have income up to twice the amount of MBR for a partnered person.</p>
</div>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example 3:</strong> A farmer who was widowed in 1992 gave her farm to her child in 1996 and partnered her new partner in 1997. The single farmers' income test is used and only the retiring farmer's income in the 3 financial years before divestment is relevant.</p>
</div>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example 4:</strong> One partner is in a nursing home and the other partner still runs the farm with their children.</p>
</div>
<p>Income is generally assessed under the provisions for ordinary income (<a href="../../../1/1/o/30">1.1.O.30</a>) and business structures, trusts and primary producers (<a href="../../../1/1/p/389">1.1.P.389</a>).</p>
<h2>Gifts</h2>
<p>When working out income for the farmers' income test, gifts made by the farmer or their partner (<a href="../../../1/1/p/85">1.1.P.85</a>) are not subject to the deeming provisions. The deeming provisions may catch gifts that do not form part of the gifted farming assets under <a href="../../../acronyms#rafs" title="Retirement assistance for farmers scheme">RAFS</a> once the applicant is granted Age.</p>
<p>If the farm was divested on or before the RAFS initiative was announced on 14 September 1997, the first date the applicant can receive income support payment under RAFS is taken as 15 September 1997.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="120">3.4.8.120</a> Start Day for Payments Accessed via RAFS, <a href="../../../4/3">4.3</a> Ordinary Income, <a href="../../../4/7">4.7</a> Business Structures, Primary Production &amp; pre-01/01/2002 Assessment of Trusts &amp; Private Companies</p>
</div>
</article>	<div id="view-last-reviewed-date">
		
		  
